black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Boy of Brell<img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle></span><br>  Posts: 373<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/22/01 7:10:50 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/jmlong/khoren_little.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dragon Question</span><hr size=1> Two things about Sev...<br>
<br>
First, He's one of those &quot;He'll be up about three days after he dies, maybe&quot; dragons from Kunark.  Hard to keep track of him, and that means he's normally taken out by groups of people with the ability to coordinate an assault within, at most, a few hours of knowing he's up.  You can't really sign folks up for him, because he's FCFS.  You just need to have a way to get a lot of people ready fast.<br>
<br>
Second, his significant attacks are an AoE fear and an infuriating long-duration (8 seconds? 10?) AoE stun which he likes to cast over and over again.  More than against Talendor or Trakanon or Vox or Nagafen or even Gorenaire, anyone too low level who has to stand inside his blast radius is going to be pretty much useless.  We did a pick-up against this guy when I was 58, and I was already close and too lazy to go get my resist stuff.  I think I got in, maybe, 5 rounds of combat in the whole fight?  Tanks pretty much have to be 55+ with enough resist to stop some of those fears and, especially, the stuns.  If they're not, they'll just be alternating between standing still and running in the other direction.<br>
<br>
Khoren Stonefall<br>
Level 60 Crusader of Marr<br>
